TY  - JOUR
T1  - Production, Inventory and Capacity Expansion Scheduling with Integer Variables
AU  - Barchi, R. H.
AU  - Sparrow, F. T.
AU  - Vemuganti, R. R.
Y1  - 1975/03/01
PY  - 1975
DA  - 1975/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.21.7.783
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.21.7.783
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 783
EP  - 793
VL  - 21
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The combined production-inventory and capacity expansion problem is modeled as a linear, integer program. The model assumes constant returns to scale in the production function of a firm which must meet, at minimum cost, deterministic demands for a single product over N periods with no backordering. A linear transformation is used to obtain an equivalent form of the model which is then decomposed into fixed cost and variable cost parts. A global optimum is obtained by enumerating on the fixed cost variables and solving transportation sub-problems with the remaining variables. Special demand and cost structures and extensions are discussed, and computational experience presented.
AB  - The combined production-inventory and capacity expansion problem is modeled as a linear, integer program. The model assumes constant returns to scale in the production function of a firm which must meet, at minimum cost, deterministic demands for a single product over N periods with no backordering. A linear transformation is used to obtain an equivalent form of the model which is then decomposed into fixed cost and variable cost parts. A global optimum is obtained by enumerating on the fixed cost variables and solving transportation sub-problems with the remaining variables. Special demand and cost structures and extensions are discussed, and computational experience presented.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.21.7.783
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.21.7.783
Y2  - 2024/03/27
