N2  - In an article of this journal [Eisner, Mark J., Robert S. Kaplan, Johh V. Soden. 1971. Admissible decision rules for the E-model of chance-constrained programming. Management Sci. 17 (5) 337?353.], Eisner, Kaplan, and Soden proposed or extended several approaches to the triangular multistage E-model of chance constrained programs with a random b-vector. On of these approaches is called the ?safety-first? approach because only decisions are allowed at any stage i which allow to take a feasible decision at any later stage.
